            <abstract>
                <p>A miniature illustrating <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3591Miracle"/> typically 
                    with as a sequence of three episodes/events, showing: first, the bishop ʾAbbās standing and distributing communion surrounded by the faithful, among whom is the woman who kisses his hand;
                    second, the bishop sitting and cutting off his hand; third, the bishop and the faithful standing in from of the icon of Mary and the Child, which has healed his hand. In the background,
                    elements of a church structure are depicted.
                </p>
